comment_data.body:
Let's keep the code overhead a little lower here.
```suggestion
                    code.putln(f"case {itr}: {self.ctuple_var} = &{self.base.result()}.f{itr % len(self.base.type.components)}; break")
```
Same below. That also avoids the need to controlling the indentation.

I also suggest using variables for the longer value parts in the f-string above, both to give them names and to make the f-string more readable.
